Pijuana wordclock
=================

This is the code for a modified version of Wordclock, made by Wouter Devinck in 2014:
http://www.instructables.com/id/Wordclock/
https://github.com/wouterdevinck/wordclock/

Our version implements a Catalan language translation of the wordclock and adds many new features, making it an amazing and multifunctional wall clock.

The hardware platform is almost identical to Wouter's project. The main difference is that we used a regular Arduino Nano and an external RTC module, instead of the custom PCB with power circuitry and Atmega328P, DS3231 chips from the original project.

The name comes from a happily newly married couple, recipient of the clock as a present.

July 2015 - September 2015
 Aleix Mercader, Antonio Camacho, Cesar August Pomerol, Enric Masdeu,
 Isabel Martínez, Jordi Aranda, Laura Mampel, Oriol Bernadó, Sergi Vaqué

 
